description: Trying a rescue a dying man's daughter, Paladin is blocked by killers and her jealous brother!
Being a bodyguard for an egotistical actor turns out to be more trouble than Paladin bargains for!

1. "Ambush" a "Heroic True Life Story" (Korean War) featuring Paul J. Wheeler of Company B, 2nd Division of the 9th Regiment who earned an Oak Leaf Cluster on his Bronze Star for his actions.
  2. "Hero First Class" a "Heroic True Life Story" (Korean War) featuring Private First Class George W. Parker of the Second Infantry Division who earned a Bronze Star for his actions..
  3. "Death Trap" a "Heroic True Life Story" featuring Los Angeles high school students Roy Cadwell and Jack Jones as they rescue a child from a burning car.
  4. "The Ammuntion Merchant" a "Heroic True Life Story" (Korean War) featuring Private First Class Raymond J. Merchant of Company A of the 27th Infantry who earned a Bronze Star with Valor for his actions.
  5. "The Goods Deliver the Goods" a "Heroic True Life Story" (Korean War) featuring Corporal Kenneth Gaddis as he earned a Silver Star for his actions.
  6. "Busy Junior Red Cross Councils" one page Red Cross ad.
  7. "Trouble is His Business" featuring Massachusett's Maurice J. Fleming as he rescues a man who was elecuted by a power line. Mr. Fleming received the Edison Electric Institute Medal for Lifesaving.
  8. "Captain Richard Fleming: Far Beyond the Call of Duty" (World War II) a two page text piece featuring USMC Captain Fleming earning a Congressional Medal of Honor posthumous for actions at Midway.
  9. "Captain Courageous" a "Heroic True Life Story" (Korean War) featuring Captain Edward Krzyzowski of Company B, 9th Regiment of the 2nd Division earning a Congressional Medal of Honor posthumous at Heartbreak Ridge.
  10. "Parents: Visit Your Schools" one page featuring November 9-15 1952 as American Education Week.
The Decepticons begin their conquest of Cybertron by rounding up Mini-Cons.
